## In Popular Culture

*   Lee is portrayed unsympathetically in *The Unvanquished*, a 1942 novel by [Howard Fast](/Howard_Fast) that focuses on [George Washington](/George_Washington) and his military campaigns.
*   Lee is featured as a secondary antagonist in the video game [Assassin's Creed III](/Assassin%27s_Creed_III), serving as second-in-command of the Colonial [Templar Order](/Knights_Templar) under [Grand Master](/Grand_master_(order)) [Haytham Kenway](/Haytham_Kenway). He is the archenemy of the protagonist [Connor Kenway](/Connor_Kenway), who ultimately kills him in an inn in 1782. He is voiced by Neil Napier. He makes a silent cameo in the game's prequel, [Assassin's Creed Rogue](/Assassin%27s_Creed_Rogue).
*   Lee and his arrest following the retreat during the [Battle of Monmouth](/Battle_of_Monmouth) are depicted in the animated television series [Liberty's Kids](/Liberty%27s_Kids).
*   Lee is a character in the first two seasons of the 2014 [AMC](/AMC_(TV_channel)) television series [Turn: Washington's Spies](/Turn:_Washington%27s_Spies), where he is blackmailed into becoming a British intelligence operative by Major [John André](/John_André). He is portrayed by Brian T. Finney.
*   Lee appears as a character in [Diana Gabaldon](/Diana_Gabaldon)'s novel *Written in My Own Heart's Blood*, part of the Outlander series.
*   Lee is a minor antagonist in the 2015 [Broadway musical](/Broadway_theatre) *Hamilton*, portrayed in the original Broadway cast by [Jon Rua](/Jon_Rua). He appears in the songs "Stay Alive" and "[Ten Duel Commandments](/Ten_Duel_Commandments)," where his duel with soldier [John Laurens](/John_Laurens) marks a pivotal point in the plot.

